[SPEAKER_00]: So the larger you are, the more you pay.

122
00:09:32,192 --> 00:09:41,158
[SPEAKER_00]: So these big, a lot of our banks are members, and they're really, by being a member, they help the smaller businesses.

123
00:09:41,938 --> 00:09:42,919
[SPEAKER_00]: That's what it's all about.

124
00:09:43,079 --> 00:09:45,440
[SPEAKER_01]: Yeah, yeah.

125
00:09:45,500 --> 00:09:50,304
[SPEAKER_01]: Helping small business, and I don't know, you guys just do a lot for the city.

126
00:09:50,344 --> 00:09:51,945
[SPEAKER_01]: It's a good thing, that's for sure.

127
00:09:51,965 --> 00:09:56,948
[SPEAKER_00]: I would say, I'll just say on that too, one of our things is

128
00:09:59,058 --> 00:10:02,560
[SPEAKER_00]: We want to encourage collaboration among the members.

129
00:10:03,040 --> 00:10:09,544
[SPEAKER_00]: So a lot of times, even if you've been here a while, you don't know of some of the new businesses we have in Medford.

130
00:10:09,844 --> 00:10:14,967
[SPEAKER_00]: Because what's great about Medford is we're still attracting a variety of businesses.

131
00:10:15,467 --> 00:10:22,011
[SPEAKER_00]: So part of our job is matching up the businesses with existing members.

132
00:10:23,992 --> 00:10:28,716
[SPEAKER_00]: They're very receptive to working together and they want to keep the business in Medford.

133
00:10:29,316 --> 00:10:32,899
[SPEAKER_00]: So we try to foster that attitude and just facilitate it.

134
00:10:33,339 --> 00:10:33,699
[SPEAKER_01]: Right.

135
00:10:33,819 --> 00:10:34,120
[SPEAKER_00]: Yeah.

136
00:10:34,220 --> 00:10:34,480
[SPEAKER_01]: Yeah.

137
00:10:34,880 --> 00:10:38,063
[SPEAKER_01]: You know, that leads me to my next question.

138
00:10:39,384 --> 00:10:41,125
[SPEAKER_01]: You know, what is the Chamber's role?

139
00:10:42,386 --> 00:10:46,369
[SPEAKER_01]: And, you know, I guess it's to help recruit business to Medford.

140
00:10:48,851 --> 00:10:49,431
[SPEAKER_00]: You know, it is.

141
00:10:51,395 --> 00:10:58,224
[SPEAKER_00]: To the extent that I want to display that Medford has a vibrant business community that is what the chamber does.

142
00:11:00,018 --> 00:11:05,443
[SPEAKER_00]: For example, recently Boston Magazine needed some photographs for an article they were doing.

143
00:11:05,643 --> 00:11:11,448
[SPEAKER_00]: They'd already written the article and they of course call me and say, I need photos and I need them in three days.

144
00:11:12,228 --> 00:11:25,339
[SPEAKER_00]: So I'm happy to respond to that quickly, go to my member photos, get some things and send it to them because any publicity for Medford I know is good for the business community.

145
00:11:26,508 --> 00:11:33,251
[SPEAKER_00]: As far as me negotiating with businesses coming in, I am not that person, that's City Hall.

146
00:11:33,271 --> 00:11:35,652
[SPEAKER_02]: It is City Hall.

147
00:11:35,752 --> 00:11:45,395
[SPEAKER_00]: Yep, they have a Director of Economic Development, which is seated in their Office of Planning, Development and Sustainability.

148
00:11:45,415 --> 00:11:46,936
[SPEAKER_00]: Okay.

149
00:11:46,956 --> 00:11:49,417
[SPEAKER_00]: I work closely with that office, but

150
00:11:50,450 --> 00:11:58,055
[SPEAKER_00]: The calls come into them, they have the framework, they have the staff, but we do have a really good working relationship.

151
00:11:58,176 --> 00:12:03,279
[SPEAKER_00]: So a lot of time I hear from the businesses that other business owners go to them.

152
00:12:04,140 --> 00:12:06,862
[SPEAKER_00]: They reach out to them and say, do you like working here?

153
00:12:07,182 --> 00:12:07,983
[SPEAKER_00]: How do I do it?

154
00:12:09,403 --> 00:12:11,164
[SPEAKER_00]: You know, they're doing their market research.

155
00:12:11,944 --> 00:12:24,669
[SPEAKER_00]: So we all, I'd say we all work together, the businesses, the chamber and the city, but it is the city's main job to recruit and we're happy to help and to display Medford in a positive light.

156
00:12:25,437 --> 00:12:33,243
[SPEAKER_01]: So you're all, you basically, you do work in a way with City Hall, you're working with established businesses, I guess, too, right?

157
00:12:33,283 --> 00:12:34,504
[SPEAKER_01]: I mean, that's all part of it.

158
00:12:35,245 --> 00:12:38,547
[SPEAKER_01]: So it's a working relationship with all of them.

159
00:12:38,647 --> 00:12:41,810
[SPEAKER_01]: I mean, it's a lot of work is what it is.

160
00:12:42,030 --> 00:12:42,370
[SPEAKER_01]: I mean.

161
00:12:43,091 --> 00:12:44,672
[SPEAKER_00]: Well, we all have the same goal, right?

162
00:12:44,892 --> 00:12:45,153
[SPEAKER_00]: Right.

163
00:12:45,173 --> 00:12:45,933
[SPEAKER_00]: That's what I mean.

164
00:12:45,973 --> 00:12:46,193
[SPEAKER_00]: Yeah.

165
00:12:46,213 --> 00:12:46,514
[SPEAKER_00]: Yeah.

166
00:12:46,834 --> 00:12:50,637
[SPEAKER_00]: And so we're happy to assist in any way.

167
00:12:52,628 --> 00:12:55,230
[SPEAKER_00]: The chamber is a staff of one, which is me.

168
00:12:55,250 --> 00:13:02,655
[SPEAKER_00]: So recruiting and going out to businesses is just not our main mission.

169
00:13:03,095 --> 00:13:03,275
[SPEAKER_00]: OK.

170
00:13:03,295 --> 00:13:04,035
[SPEAKER_01]: All right.

171
00:13:04,316 --> 00:13:05,216
[SPEAKER_01]: All right.

172
00:13:06,357 --> 00:13:09,079
[SPEAKER_01]: So I mean, it is a tight knit community method.

173
00:13:09,779 --> 00:13:12,541
[SPEAKER_01]: And so I'm going to ask this again.

174
00:13:12,581 --> 00:13:13,842
