[SPEAKER_00]: Yeah.

195
00:14:32,669 --> 00:14:40,132
[SPEAKER_00]: You know, I have a board and we have committees, and they're very committed to helping the chamber.

196
00:14:41,032 --> 00:14:48,755
[SPEAKER_00]: So I am grateful for all their work, because that's the only way we're able to accomplish so much is with our strong board.

197
00:14:49,838 --> 00:15:00,862
[SPEAKER_00]: And there are times that we need to write to City Hall or call City Hall and be like, we don't think these policies are serving our businesses.

198
00:15:01,082 --> 00:15:08,145
[SPEAKER_00]: Or this is why these policies should be adapted so that the business are able to operate.

199
00:15:08,585 --> 00:15:17,788
[SPEAKER_00]: And a lot of times, some of our conversations are, oh, I didn't realize, no one is trying to curtail business.

200
00:15:18,235 --> 00:15:18,836
[SPEAKER_02]: Right.

201
00:15:19,356 --> 00:15:21,117
[SPEAKER_00]: You know, things like that.

202
00:15:22,018 --> 00:15:25,001
[SPEAKER_00]: Now, you know, businesses pay a lot of taxes.

203
00:15:25,521 --> 00:15:26,442
[SPEAKER_01]: Yes, they do.

204
00:15:27,683 --> 00:15:28,944
[SPEAKER_00]: They really pay a lot.

205
00:15:29,004 --> 00:15:31,086
[SPEAKER_00]: So we need to respect their opinions.

206
00:15:31,226 --> 00:15:35,269
[SPEAKER_00]: And so a lot, you know, it's a working relationship.

207
00:15:35,329 --> 00:15:37,010
[SPEAKER_00]: And I'm proud of that relationship.

208
00:15:38,892 --> 00:15:42,515
[SPEAKER_00]: And, you know, it's something that we have

209
00:15:43,204 --> 00:15:51,228
[SPEAKER_00]: meetings on a regular basis, and I do appreciate their support, and I also appreciate the fact that they'll reach out to us to ask questions.

210
00:15:51,988 --> 00:15:52,808
[SPEAKER_01]: Okay, yeah.

211
00:15:53,149 --> 00:15:58,451
[SPEAKER_01]: So you get a lot of, now, sort of a follow-up.

