00:28:38,034 --> 00:28:38,315
[SPEAKER_00]: Yeah.

389
00:28:38,435 --> 00:28:41,197
[SPEAKER_00]: And it's it's nice to have them in South Method.

390
00:28:41,237 --> 00:28:44,219
[SPEAKER_00]: We have Allegria, which is an acai place.

391
00:28:44,459 --> 00:28:45,820
[SPEAKER_00]: Right.

392
00:28:46,440 --> 00:28:48,942
[SPEAKER_00]: We have such variety.

393
00:28:48,962 --> 00:28:53,305
[SPEAKER_00]: And, you know, we're lucky.

394
00:28:53,325 --> 00:28:58,089
[SPEAKER_00]: And by having these businesses all in the chamber,

395
00:28:59,462 --> 00:29:03,465
[SPEAKER_00]: we can hopefully encourage even Medford residents to try somewhere new.

396
00:29:03,506 --> 00:29:04,546
[SPEAKER_01]: Yeah, yeah.

397
00:29:05,267 --> 00:29:06,608
[SPEAKER_01]: I go to Mrs. Murphy's.

398
00:29:07,409 --> 00:29:08,990
[SPEAKER_01]: He's got the Ford Tavern, too.

399
00:29:09,931 --> 00:29:10,952
[SPEAKER_01]: Another good restaurant.

400
00:29:10,992 --> 00:29:12,533
[SPEAKER_01]: Yeah, we're very lucky.

401
00:29:12,653 --> 00:29:19,119
[SPEAKER_01]: It's been a lot of established restaurants, and we got quite a few new ones.

402
00:29:19,779 --> 00:29:21,401
[SPEAKER_01]: And I've been to a lot of them, so.

403
00:29:21,421 --> 00:29:21,921
[SPEAKER_00]: Well, that's good.

404
00:29:22,241 --> 00:29:27,286
[SPEAKER_00]: And I do have to mention that Barry Rafferty, who owns both those restaurants, joined our board.

405
00:29:27,746 --> 00:29:28,067
[SPEAKER_01]: Right.

406
00:29:28,447 --> 00:29:33,431
[SPEAKER_00]: So it's nice to have the assistance and to have that insight into those industries.

407
00:29:34,472 --> 00:29:35,914
[SPEAKER_00]: We welcome that on our board.

408
00:29:35,934 --> 00:29:41,579
[SPEAKER_00]: We want to have representation from the different industries so that we can serve everyone.

409
00:29:42,079 --> 00:29:43,561
[SPEAKER_01]: Yeah, I live right above Barry.

410
00:29:44,911 --> 00:29:46,271
[SPEAKER_01]: Yeah, at the Fort Allen.

411
00:29:46,572 --> 00:29:47,612
[SPEAKER_01]: He's my neighbor.

412
00:29:48,072 --> 00:29:50,673
[SPEAKER_01]: Yeah, great guy, Barry Rafferty, the family.

413
00:29:50,733 --> 00:29:52,073
[SPEAKER_01]: Very, very nice people.

414
00:29:53,953 --> 00:29:56,494
[SPEAKER_01]: Unfortunately, it's that time again.

415
00:29:56,514 --> 00:29:59,335
[SPEAKER_01]: Laura, I really do.

416
00:29:59,415 --> 00:30:03,336
[SPEAKER_01]: I want to thank you for joining us on Method Happenings.

417
00:30:03,836 --> 00:30:11,217
[SPEAKER_01]: And we, all of us at Method Happenings, wish continued success to you, to the Method Chamber of Commerce.

418
00:30:11,637 --> 00:30:13,458
[SPEAKER_01]: And just, you know, keep up the good work.

419
00:30:14,383 --> 00:30:15,784
[SPEAKER_01]: Thank you so much for joining us.

420
00:30:15,824 --> 00:30:17,365
[SPEAKER_01]: It's been our pleasure.

421
00:30:18,185 --> 00:30:18,926
[SPEAKER_00]: All right, thank you.

422
00:30:19,006 --> 00:30:26,531
[SPEAKER_00]: Thank you, John, for having, thank you for inviting me and for doing what you do for Medford, because I agree with you.

423
00:30:26,711 --> 00:30:29,713
[SPEAKER_00]: The more we can share with people the great things.

424
00:30:30,373 --> 00:30:31,514
[SPEAKER_00]: I did forget one thing.

425
00:30:31,834 --> 00:30:32,134
[SPEAKER_00]: Go ahead.

426
00:30:32,555 --> 00:30:34,376
[SPEAKER_00]: You're doing the Citizen of the Year.

427
00:30:35,056 --> 00:30:38,058
[SPEAKER_00]: I forgot the Citizen of the Year nominations are now out.

428
00:30:38,619 --> 00:30:43,522
[SPEAKER_00]: If anyone wants to nominate someone for Citizen of the Year, the form is on our website.

429
00:30:44,042 --> 00:30:44,702
[SPEAKER_00]: Good to know.

430
00:30:44,943 --> 00:30:46,644
[SPEAKER_01]: Good to know.

431
00:30:46,844 --> 00:30:49,225
[SPEAKER_01]: What's the Citizen of the Year?

432
00:30:49,245 --> 00:30:50,326
[SPEAKER_01]: What's the date for that?

433
00:30:50,346 --> 00:30:51,146
[SPEAKER_01]: Do you have a date?

434
00:30:51,987 --> 00:30:53,007
[SPEAKER_01]: I'm curious.

435
00:30:53,307 --> 00:30:53,648
[SPEAKER_00]: Sure.

436
00:30:53,788 --> 00:30:56,109
[SPEAKER_00]: It'll be awarded at our luncheon on May 4th.

437
00:30:56,469 --> 00:30:57,590
[SPEAKER_01]: May 4th luncheon.

438
00:30:57,810 --> 00:30:59,371
[SPEAKER_01]: And that's the Citizen of the Year.

439
00:30:59,791 --> 00:31:00,071
[SPEAKER_00]: Yep.

440
00:31:01,772 --> 00:31:04,614
[SPEAKER_00]: And the nominations are due by April 2nd.

441
00:31:05,154 --> 00:31:05,554
[SPEAKER_01]: OK.

442
00:31:06,055 --> 00:31:06,875
[SPEAKER_01]: Sounds great.

443
00:31:07,636 --> 00:31:08,296
[SPEAKER_01]: Thank you, John.

444
00:31:08,556 --> 00:31:08,896
[SPEAKER_01]: Oh, no.

445
00:31:08,936 --> 00:31:09,717
[SPEAKER_01]: Thank you.

446
00:31:09,837 --> 00:31:11,278
[SPEAKER_01]: It's been our pleasure.

447
00:31:12,838 --> 00:31:14,559
[SPEAKER_01]: I'm glad we did this show.

448
00:31:14,680 --> 00:31:17,201
[SPEAKER_01]: It's important and it's good for Method.

449
00:31:17,241 --> 00:31:20,363
[SPEAKER_01]: So, all right, we'll see you and thank you so much.

450
00:31:20,384 --> 00:31:21,444
[SPEAKER_01]: Have a great day.

451
00:31:21,724 --> 00:31:22,185
[SPEAKER_01]: You too.

452
00:31:23,346 --> 00:31:31,471
[SPEAKER_01]: I also want to take a minute to thank everyone who has been watching the show and thank you for your feedback.

453
00:31:32,292 --> 00:31:39,617
[SPEAKER_01]: If you would like to appear on the show, Method Happenings, you can contact us at MethodHappenings.org.

454
00:31:42,062 --> 00:31:44,164
[SPEAKER_01]: 02155 at gmail.com.

455
00:31:44,964 --> 00:31:52,291
[SPEAKER_01]: You will be able to watch replays of this program on Method Community Media Access Channel.

456
00:31:53,052 --> 00:31:57,476
[SPEAKER_01]: It's usually Monday, Wednesday, and Friday at 6 to 7 p.m.

457
00:31:59,418 --> 00:32:05,203
[SPEAKER_01]: I also want to mention to check out our website, methodhappenings.com.

458
00:32:07,413 --> 00:32:12,778
[SPEAKER_01]: And you can now either view or listen to the podcast of this program.

459
00:32:12,798 --> 00:32:19,144
[SPEAKER_01]: And you can also find us on YouTube and on Facebook at Method Happenings.

460
00:32:19,704 --> 00:32:25,910
[SPEAKER_01]: So for the Method Happenings team, Paul, Marco, Bruce, and myself, I'm John Petrella.

461
00:32:27,151 --> 00:32:29,614
[SPEAKER_01]: And remember Method, stay informed.

462
00:32:29,974 --> 00:32:30,395
[SPEAKER_01]: Thank you.

